      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INSTA WORTHY (4) resumed and demolished the Maidens this track/trip by 3.1L. Had switched from Matt Dunn in NSW and is still shy of his best. Has the inside barrier and the in-form Morrison sticks board. He can take the next step. RAFF VADER (6) resumed in the same race and needed the outing. Just missed this track/trip two back, and Cormack is reunited, replacing Wiggins. Quick improvement is likely.  NOTTINGTON PRINCE (1) is free running and followed a first-up Maiden win at Townsville with a 2.5L defeat there over 1200m in an Open 3. Has good ability but has to come back 250m on a 9-day return and with a number of gear changes. HAPHAZARD (3) will be fitter and race forward from the much better barrier. He will be in it for a long way.",
